<p><b>8) Investments in Affiliated Retail Companies</b> </p>
<p>All U.S. Kmart footwear departments are operated under license
agreements with the Meldisco subsidiaries of Melville Corporation,
substantially all of which are 49% owned by Kmart and 51% owned
by Melville. Fees and income earned under the license agreements
in 1995, 1994 and 1993 of $182, $204 and $195, respectively, are
included in licensee fees and other income. Kmart's equity in the
income of footwear departments in Kmart stores and dividends
received were as follows: </p>
